var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"Homepage","text":"css add shadow <p>Hi, this is the learning blog of VocabWise. We are documenting our leanring process when building our product.</p>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0000-example.html","title":"Example","text":"<p>This is an example post.</p>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0000-example.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<ul> <li>Example<ul> <li>Overview</li> <li>Section1<ul> <li>Subsection1</li> </ul> </li> <li>Section2</li> </ul> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0000-example.html#section1","title":"Section1","text":""},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0000-example.html#subsection1","title":"Subsection1","text":"<p>Hello, world!</p>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0000-example.html#section2","title":"Section2","text":"<p>References:</p>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0003-tcf_canada.html","title":"How to Prepare for TCF Canada","text":"<p>This post is about how to prepare for TCF Canada.</p>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0003-tcf_canada.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<ul> <li>How to Prepare for TCF Canada<ul> <li>Overview</li> <li>Introduction to TCF Canada (TODO)<ul> <li>TCF-NCLC Equivalency</li> <li>Plan for Learning TCF Canada (TODO)</li> </ul> </li> <li>Introduction to PTE Core (TODO)</li> </ul> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0003-tcf_canada.html#introduction-to-tcf-canada-todo","title":"Introduction to TCF Canada (TODO)","text":""},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0003-tcf_canada.html#tcf-nclc-equivalency","title":"TCF-NCLC Equivalency","text":"<p>According to IRCC's official document, the TCF-NCLC Equivalency is as follows:</p> NCLC level Speaking Listening Reading Writing 10 16-20 549-699 549-699 16-20 9 14-15 523-548 524-548 14-15 8 12-13 503-522 499-523 12-13 7 10-11 458-502 453-498 10-11 6 7-9 398-457 406-452 7-9 5 6 369-397 375-405 6 4 4-5 331-368 342-374 4-5"},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0003-tcf_canada.html#plan-for-learning-tcf-canada-todo","title":"Plan for Learning TCF Canada (TODO)","text":""},{"location":"blog/Posts/drafts/0003-tcf_canada.html#introduction-to-pte-core-todo","title":"Introduction to PTE Core (TODO)","text":"<p>Most people are familiar with English language tests like IELTS and CELPIP. Here, we introduce PTE Core, another English test accepted by IRCC. It is often considered easier and faster to prepare.</p> <p>According to IRCC's official document, the PTE Core-CLB Equivalency is as follows:</p> CLB level Speaking Listening Reading Writing 10 89-90 89-90 88-90 90 9 84-88 82-88 78-87 88-89 8 76-83 71-81 69-77 79-87 7 68-75 60-70 60-68 69-78 6 59-67 50-59 51-59 60-68 5 51-58 39-49 42-50 51-59 4 42-50 28-38 33-41 41-50 3 34-41 18-27 24-32 32-40 <p>References:</p> <p>References:</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html","title":"Introduction to UV","text":"<p>UV can serve as a faster and more efficient package manager for python. It's very easy to switch to uv if you used to use conda and pip. Here are the basic usage of uv.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<ul> <li>Introduction to UV<ul> <li>Overview</li> <li>How to install UV</li> <li>How to manage the virtual environment via UV</li> <li>\\(\\star\\) How to manage the project via UV</li> <li>How to manage the python version via UV</li> <li>Link to UV's doc</li> </ul> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html#how-to-install-uv","title":"How to install UV","text":"<pre><code>curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html#how-to-manage-the-virtual-environment-via-uv","title":"How to manage the virtual environment via UV","text":"<p>It's extremely easy to switch to uv if you used to use conda and pip. But uv is much more faster than conda. Here is a way similar to conda and pip to manage the python version and the dependencies via uv.</p> <p>To create a virtual environment: <pre><code>uv venv\n</code></pre></p> <p>To create a virtual environment at my-name(specific path): <pre><code>uv venv my-name\n</code></pre></p> <p>To create a virtual environment with specific python version: <pre><code>uv venv --python 3.11\n</code></pre></p> <p>To activate the environment: <pre><code>source .venv/bin/activate\n</code></pre></p> <p>To deactivate the environment: <pre><code>deactivate\n</code></pre></p> <p>The dependencies management in virtual environment is very similar to pip.</p> <p>To install a package: <pre><code>uv pip install &lt;package&gt;\n</code></pre> To uninstall a package: <pre><code>uv pip uninstall &lt;package&gt;\n</code></pre> To list installed packages: <pre><code>uv pip list\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html#star-how-to-manage-the-project-via-uv","title":"\\(\\star\\) How to manage the project via UV","text":"<p>What is more convienient and elegant is that uv can manage the project along with its environment as well as corresponding dependencies. There is another way to manage the project and dependencies.</p> <p>In each project, uv will create <code>pyproject.toml</code> file to manage the dependencies and update the environment according to the <code>pyproject.toml</code> file. Here is the way to manage the project and dependencies.</p> <p>To create a new project,cd to the project directory and run: <pre><code>uv init\n</code></pre> uv will create a <code>pyproject.toml</code> file.</p> <p>To create virtual environment according to the <code>pyproject.toml</code> file: <pre><code>uv venv\n</code></pre></p> <p>To update the environment according to the <code>pyproject.toml</code> file: <pre><code>uv sync\n</code></pre> To run the program in the corresponding environment: <pre><code>uv run &lt;command&gt;\n</code></pre> <code>uv run</code> can directly run the program in the corresponding environment. It's similar to <code>source .venv/bin/activate</code> and <code>python &lt;command&gt;</code>. </p> <p>Before running the program, uv will also automatically update the environment according to the pyproject.toml file. So <code>uv run</code> is the most convenient way to run any program in this project.</p> <p>For example, if you want to run the program <code>main.py</code>, you can run: <pre><code>uv run main.py\n</code></pre></p> <p>if you want to run the shell script <code>script.sh</code>, you can run: <pre><code>uv run zsh script.sh\n</code></pre></p> <p>To add the dependencies in the <code>pyproject.toml</code> file: <pre><code>uv add &lt;package&gt;\n</code></pre></p> <p>To remove the dependencies in the <code>pyproject.toml</code> file: <pre><code>uv remove &lt;package&gt;\n</code></pre></p> <p>To upgrade the dependencies in the <code>pyproject.toml</code> file: <pre><code>uv lock --upgrade-package &lt;package&gt;\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html#how-to-manage-the-python-version-via-uv","title":"How to manage the python version via UV","text":"<p>To install the latest version of python: <pre><code>uv python install\n</code></pre> To install a specific version of python: <pre><code>uv python install 3.10\n</code></pre> To view available versions: <pre><code>uv python list\n</code></pre></p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/04/11/introduction-to-uv.html#link-to-uvs-doc","title":"Link to UV's doc","text":""},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html","title":"How to Apply for PR via Learning French and Express Entry","text":"<p>This blog explains how to apply for permanent residence (PR) in Canada through Express Entry via French language proficiency. We will begin with an overview of the Express Entry system, focusing on the Canadian Experience Class program and French-language proficiency category.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<ul> <li>How to Apply for PR via Learning French and Express Entry<ul> <li>Overview</li> <li>Brief Introduction of Express Entry</li> <li>Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS)</li> <li>Eligibility for EE Entry and the Three Immigration programs<ul> <li>Immigration Programs</li> <li>\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) Eligibility for Immigration Programs</li> <li>Explanation of the Eligibility of Canadian Experience Class<ul> <li>What is NOC and TEER?</li> <li>How to Check Your TEER Level?</li> <li>Example of NOC and TEER</li> </ul> </li> </ul> </li> <li>Current Categories<ul> <li>All Current Categories</li> <li>\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) French-language proficiency Category Eligibility<ul> <li>TCFCanada-NCLC Equivalency</li> </ul> </li> <li>\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) French-language proficiency Category Invitation Procedure</li> <li>\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) Information of French-language proficiency Category in Recent Round</li> </ul> </li> <li>Conclusion</li> <li>References<ul> <li>Official Government Resources</li> <li>NOC and Occupation Classification Tools</li> </ul> </li> </ul> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#brief-introduction-of-express-entry","title":"Brief Introduction of Express Entry","text":"<p>Express Entry is the Canadian government's online system for managing skilled worker immigration. In this guide, we will use <code>EE Entry</code> to refer to the Express Entry system.</p> <p>EE Entry is a point-based system with different immigration programs and selection categories. Understanding both is critical to maximizing your Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score. In this section, we briefly introduce the Canadian Experience Class and the French-language proficiency category. For more details, see EE Eligibility.</p> <p></p> <p>There are three main structural components of EE Entry:</p> <ol> <li>Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS): Calculate your CRS points, which is not only used in eligibility but also used in ranking.</li> <li>Immigration Programs: Determine your eligibility to enter the EE pool.</li> <li>Current Categories: Award additional points in targeted rounds or encourage more applications by requiring lower points.</li> </ol> <p>To begin, you must first qualify for one of the immigration programs, then explore categories to boost your score.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#comprehensive-ranking-system-crs","title":"Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS)","text":"<p>CRS Points System is a key component of EE Entry. It is used to determine candidates' eligibility and rank them in the pool. Here is the official calculator. Generally, young people with relatively good educational backgrounds can easily earn CRS points sufficient to pass the French-language proficiency category.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#eligibility-for-ee-entry-and-the-three-immigration-programs","title":"Eligibility for EE Entry and the Three <code>Immigration programs</code>","text":""},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#immigration-programs","title":"Immigration Programs","text":"<p>According to the official website, EE Entry includes three immigration programs:</p> <ol> <li>Canadian Experience Class</li> <li>Federal Skilled Worker Program</li> <li>Federal Skilled Trades Program</li> </ol>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#star-eligibility-for-immigration-programs","title":"\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) Eligibility for Immigration Programs","text":"<p>Each program has distinct eligibility requirements. Applicants must first identify the one they qualify for to enter the EE pool.</p> <p>We'll focus on the Canadian Experience Class:</p> <ol> <li>Be in one or more NOC categories: TEER 0, 1, 2, or 3<ol> <li>Your experience can be in more than one NOC.</li> <li>See explanation of NOC in the Eligibility of Canadian Experience Class section.</li> </ol> </li> <li>Be gained in Canada while authorized to work under temporary resident status<ol> <li>If you worked remotely, you must have been physically in Canada and working for a Canadian employer.</li> </ol> </li> <li>Show that you performed:<ol> <li>The actions in the lead statement of the NOC job description</li> <li>Most of the main duties listed</li> </ol> </li> <li>Be paid work (you must have been paid wages or earned commission\u2014volunteer work or unpaid internships don't count)</li> <li>Be at least 1 year of work or 1,560 hours total (30 hours per week) in the 3 years before you apply</li> </ol>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#explanation-of-the-eligibility-of-canadian-experience-class","title":"Explanation of the Eligibility of Canadian Experience Class","text":""},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#what-is-noc-and-teer","title":"What is NOC and TEER?","text":"<p>The National Occupation Classification (NOC) system is used by Canada to classify occupations. The updated NOC uses Training, Education, Experience and Responsibilities (TEER) levels. Only TEER 0, 1, 2, or 3 jobs count toward the Canadian Experience Class.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#how-to-check-your-teer-level","title":"How to Check Your TEER Level?","text":"<ol> <li>Use the Find your NOC tool to search your job title.</li> <li>Cross-reference the NOC code in the official NOC website to verify job duties.</li> <li>If it matches and falls under TEER 0\u20133, congratulations! You're eligible for CEC.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#example-of-noc-and-teer","title":"Example of NOC and TEER","text":"<p>Take an example of a Graduate Student in Canada, the NOC code of <code>Post-secondary teaching and research assistants</code> is <code>41201</code> with <code>TEER 1</code> level, as we can see in the NOC Website. </p> <p>We can then see in the Search Result of NOC Website, Both Teaching Assistants and Research Assistants are included in TEER 1. So if you were serving as a TA or RA in Canada for at least 1 year, you are eligible for Canadian Experience Class Program.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#current-categories","title":"<code>Current Categories</code>","text":""},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#all-current-categories","title":"All Current Categories","text":"<p>Once you're eligible for one of the three programs, you can increase your CRS score through the following six <code>Current categories</code>:</p> <ol> <li>French-language proficiency</li> <li>Healthcare and social services occupations  </li> <li>Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) occupations  </li> <li>Trade occupations  </li> <li>Agriculture and agri-food occupations  </li> <li>Education occupations</li> </ol> <p>This guide focuses on the French-language proficiency category.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#star-french-language-proficiency-category-eligibility","title":"\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) French-language proficiency Category Eligibility","text":"<ol> <li>Meet the minimum criteria for Express Entry, including being eligible for 1 of the 3 immigration programs it covers</li> <li>Have French-language test results that show a minimum score of 7 in all 4 language abilities on the Niveaux de comp\u00e9tence linguistique canadiens<ol> <li>The equivalency between TCFCanada and NCLC is shown in the TCFCanada-NCLC Equivalency section.</li> </ol> </li> <li>Meet all of the requirements in the instructions for that round</li> </ol>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#tcfcanada-nclc-equivalency","title":"TCFCanada-NCLC Equivalency","text":"<p>TCFCanada is one of the French-language exam used by IRCC to evaluate candidates' French-language proficiency. According to IRCC's official document, the TCFCanada-NCLC Equivalency is as follows:</p> NCLC level Speaking Listening Reading Writing 10 16-20 549-699 549-699 16-20 9 14-15 523-548 524-548 14-15 8 12-13 503-522 499-523 12-13 7 10-11 458-502 453-498 10-11 6 7-9 398-457 406-452 7-9 5 6 369-397 375-405 6 4 4-5 331-368 342-374 4-5"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#star-french-language-proficiency-category-invitation-procedure","title":"\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) French-language proficiency Category Invitation Procedure","text":"<p>When holding a category-based round of invitations, IRCC will:</p> <ol> <li>Rank candidates in the pool who meet the category requirements</li> <li>Invite top-ranking candidates to apply for permanent residence</li> </ol> <p>For the most up-to-date information, refer to the official category-based selection page.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#star-information-of-french-language-proficiency-category-in-recent-round","title":"\ud83d\ude80 \\(\\star\\) Information of French-language proficiency Category in Recent Round","text":"<p>As shown by IRCC, IRCC invited 23,500 people in 2024, the highest score of CRS in French-language proficiency category is 478, the lowest score is 336. Generally speaking, if you are eligible for French-language proficiency category and have reasonably good CRS points, you have a good chance to be invited.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#conclusion","title":"Conclusion","text":"<p>The French-language proficiency category has been relatively stable in recent years. If you are eligible for French-language proficiency category and have reasonably good CRS points, you have a good chance to be invited.</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#references","title":"References","text":"<p>For the most up-to-date information, please refer to the official IRCC Express Entry website and related documentation. Here are all of the links we referenced in this blog:</p>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#official-government-resources","title":"Official Government Resources","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Express Entry - Main portal for Canada's Express Entry immigration system, providing comprehensive information about the application process.</p> </li> <li> <p>EE Eligibility - Detailed eligibility requirements for all three Express Entry programs.</p> </li> <li> <p>CRS Calculator - Official tool to calculate your Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score.</p> </li> <li> <p>Canadian Experience Class - Specific requirements and guidelines for the Canadian Experience Class program.</p> </li> <li> <p>Category-based Selection - Information about category-based invitation rounds including French-language proficiency category.</p> </li> <li> <p>Express Entry Rounds - Historical data and statistics of all Express Entry invitation rounds.</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"blog/2025/05/31/ee-french.html#noc-and-occupation-classification-tools","title":"NOC and Occupation Classification Tools","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Find your NOC tool - Government tool to search and identify your National Occupation Classification (NOC) code.</p> </li> <li> <p>Official NOC website - Complete database of National Occupation Classification codes and job descriptions.</p> </li> <li> <p>NOC Code 41201 Profile - Specific profile for Post-secondary teaching and research assistants (example used in the blog).</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"blog/archive/2025.html","title":"2025","text":""},{"location":"blog/category/french.html","title":"French","text":""},{"location":"blog/category/ee-entry.html","title":"EE Entry","text":""},{"location":"blog/category/tools.html","title":"Tools","text":""}]}